IBADAN – The Provost and Deputy Provost of the University of Ibadan College of Medicine, Professors Ezekiel Olapade-Olaopa and Obafunke Denloye respectively have tested positive to Coronavirus. Olapade-Olaopa, who made this known in a Whatsapp group message Sunday morning, said “Dear colleagues, I wish to inform you that the deputy provost and I tested positive for the COVID-19 following the tests done on Friday. “Although we are both asymptomatic, we have gone into self-isolation for the 14 days while our contacts are being observed closely to determine if they should also be tested.” (ThePodiumMedia) By Gabriel Agbeja Abuja - The Nigerian Academy of Science (NAS) has urged the Federal Government to allocate one per cent of the annual budget to Research and Develop (R&D) to boost Gross Domestic Product (GDP). The former NAS President, Prof. Oye Ibidapo-Obe gave the advice   at a two-day workshop organised by… March 8, 2018 In "News" By Ibukun Emiola Ibadan --  The Minister of Health, Prof. Isaac Adewole, and other eminent Nigerians on Thursday in Ibadan paid tributes to an emeritus professor of medecine, Oluwole Akande, who clocked 80 years. They spoke at a symposium organised by a Committee of Mentees to celebrate the 80th birthday… December 20, 2018 In "News" Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The Chief Medical Director, University College Hospital, Ibadan, Prof Jesse A Otegbayo, has tested positive for coronavirus. This was disclosed in a statement personally signed by the CMD. The Statement reads: “On Monday 23rd March, we commenced a 12man quarterly board meeting which was meant to… March 29, 2020 In "Top Stories"